  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>From 1st level, you have <strong>darkvision </strong>with a range of 120 feet.</p>\n<p>When you reach 3rd level in this class, you learn the @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-spells.95HlMKeNkm1x8LIQ]{Darkness} spell, which doesn't count against your number of sorcerer spells known. In addition, you can cast it by spending 2 sorcery points or by expending a spell slot. If you cast it with sorcery points, you can see through the darkness created by the spell.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: Create two copies of @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-spells.95HlMKeNkm1x8LIQ]{Darkness}</em><em> on your character. Set the first copy to Always Prepared.</em></p>\n<p><em>For the second copy, set Preparation Mode to Innate and Resource Consumption to Item Uses: Font of Magic: 2</em></p>\n</section>",
